1. FR3QU3NCY? 2. R0CKST4R! 3. PR4CTI1C3? 4. 1M0R3! 5. R0BL0X! 6. BR33Z3! 7. S1SSY! 8. K3YS! 9. Y0U 4ND 1? - 1nt3rlud3 Review of the album "MANSLAUGHTER SQUAD" Rated ⅕ An album may occasionally appear that will make you wonder how it was able to leave the confines of a basement studio and make it to streaming services. A bunch of buddies came up with "MANSLAUGHTER SQUAD" as a way to show off their musical abilities. This album serves as a terrible reminder that not all artistic endeavors are successful, with cringe-inducing vocals and subpar self-produced tracks. It is clear from the opening track that "MANSLAUGHTER SQUAD" has trouble getting into a groove. The beats are shallow and unoriginal, plainly the consequence of novice production. They have the impression that they were made with simple software, paying little attention to composition, arrangement, or sound design. The beats frequently conflict with the vocal attempts, resulting in a dissonance that is difficult to ignore. The vocals themselves could be the poorest aspect of the record. The vocalists appear to have difficulty controlling their vocal pitch, tone, and volume. It appears as though they are still getting the hang of maintaining pitch or selecting a melody that works for their voices. It is challenging to relate to the words and to understand any possible lyrical depth that could be concealed beneath the surface because of the singers' lack of vocal ability. The narrative and emotional expression attempts come out as clunky and childish. The lyrics sometimes lack clarity, which makes listening confusing rather than engaging. It's obvious that prior to starting the recording process, more focus should have been placed on improving the songwriting. Another noticeable flaw with this record is the production quality. The mix is off-balance, and the vocals frequently get lost behind the poor beats. This disparity emphasizes even more how little refinement and professionalism can be anticipated from projects that are even self-produced. "MANSLAUGHTER SQUAD" fails to provide a competitive experience in the current musical scene, where independent artists may produce high-quality works from the convenience of their own homes. In summary, "MANSLAUGHTER SQUAD" is a collection of songs that sadly falls short in terms of vocal delivery, and production. The work put into this project is laudable, but it's obvious that more time and consideration were needed to polish the musical components and provide a more seamless and delightful listening experience. This album is a reminder that musical talent and originality should be nurtured over time and refined before being shared with a larger audience.

.fmbot BOT 8/14/2023 4:12 AM
Using Spotify and tracking is out of sync?
.fmbot uses your Last.fm account for knowing what you listen to. Unfortunately, Last.fm and Spotify sometimes have issues keeping up to date with your current song, which can cause .fm and other commands to lag behind the song you're currently listening to. First, .fmbot is not affiliated with Last.fm. Your music is tracked by Last.fm, and not by .fmbot. This means that this is a Last.fm issue and not an .fmbot issue. We can't fix it for you, but we can give you some tips that worked for others. Some things you can try that usually work:
  • Restarting your Spotify application
  • Disconnecting and reconnecting Spotify in your Last.fm settings If the two options above don't work, check out the complete guide for this issue on the Last.fm support forums.
